\f0\fs52 \cf2 Vermont Burgers
\b\fs38 \cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa160\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf3 INGREDIENTS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0 \cf2 Makes 20 (10 turkey, 10 beef).\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b \cf2 		FOR THE TURKEY BURGERS
\b0 \cf2 \
    	1 pound ground white-meat turkey\
		1 pound ground dark-meat turkey\
		1/2 cup fromage blanc or pureed ricotta cheese\
		1/2 cup coarsely chopped fresh flat-leaf parsley\
		2 teaspoons finely chopped fresh sage\
		2 garlic cloves, minced\
		Coarse salt and freshly ground pepper\
		Extra-virgin olive oil, for brushing\
\ls1\ilvl0
\b \cf2 		FOR THE BEEF BURGERS
\b0 \cf2 \
		2 pounds ground beef, preferably grass-fed\
		Coarse salt and freshly ground pepper\
\ls1\ilvl0
\b \cf2 		FOR GRILLING
\b0 \cf2 \
       Vegetable oil, for brushing\
\ls1\ilvl0
\b \cf2 		FOR SERVING
\b0 \cf2 \
		20 hamburger buns, split\
		1 stick unsalted butter, softened\
		\
    	Garnish: {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.marthastewart.com/recipe/extra-special-sauce"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Extra-Special Sauce}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.marthastewart.com/recipe/homemade-beer-spring-onion-mustard"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Homemade Beer-Spring Onion Mustard}}, pickles, thin cheddar cheese slices, lettuce, and tomato slices\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0\cf2 		
\b \cf3 \
DIRECTIONS\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0 \cf2 		For the turkey burgers: Arrange 10 (4-inch) parchment squares on a tray. Gently mix together turkey, cheese, parsley, sage, garlic, 2 teaspoons salt, and 1 teaspoon pepper. Shape meat into 10 (3-ounce) patties (3 1/2 inches in diameter and 1/2 inch thick). Transfer patties to parchment.\
		For the beef burgers: Shape meat into 10 patties (see turkey burger instructions above).\
		Refrigerate patties for at least 1 hour.\
		    	Heat grill to medium-high; brush grates with vegetable oil.\
		Cook the turkey burgers: Brush tops with olive oil. Flip burgers onto grill, peeling off paper. Grill for 3 minutes. Brush tops with olive oil. Flip, and grill until cooked through, about 2 minutes more.\
		Cook the beef burgers: Season burgers with salt and pepper. Grill for 4 minutes. Flip, and grill until cooked through, 2 to 3 minutes more (6 minutes total for medium-rare, 7 minutes total for medium).\
		To serve burgers: Brush buns with butter, and grill until browning around edges, about 30 seconds. Sandwich burgers between buns, garnished with desired toppings.\
