\ls2\ilvl0\cf2 		3 tablespoons safflower oil\
		2 1/2 pounds thinly sliced Vidalia onions\
		1/2 cup mustard powder (from 2 containers)\
		1 tablespoon salt\
		1 teaspoon turmeric\
		1/3 cup cider vinegar\
		1 cup pale ale\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural
\cf2 	
\b \cf3 \
DIRECTIONS\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\b0 \cf2 		Heat a large skillet over high heat. Add safflower oil, and swirl to coat. Reduce heat to medium. Cook Vidalia onions, stirring often, until very soft, about 30 minutes. Stir in mustard powder, salt, and turmeric. Cook, stirring often, for 3 minutes. Stir in cider vinegar, and raise heat to high. Add pale ale, and cook, stirring often, until mixture is thick, about 5 minutes. Let cool completely.\
